  <main class="container">
    <section class="section-header">
      <h2>Glossary of A/B Testing Terms</h2>
      <p>Simple definitions and friendly analogies.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="accordion">
      <details class="accordion-item">
        <summary><span>Conversion Rate</span></summary>
        <div class="acc-body">Think of it like a batting average. If 100 people visit and 5 buy, your CR is 5%.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion-item">
        <summary><span>Lift</span></summary>
        <div class="acc-body">How much better (or worse) B did vs A. Like measuring the improvement in test scores.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion-item">
        <summary><span>Statistical Significance</span></summary>
        <div class="acc-body">Means you're confident the result isn't just random noise. Think: not just a lucky shot.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion-item">
        <summary><span>Variant</span></summary>
        <div class="acc-body">The version you're testing against your original (control).</div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <p>Learn the language of data, one term at a time.</p>
  </footer>

